Filter to relevant species, create 4 category temporal term

analysis.bumbles.df <- analysis.bumbles.df %>%
  filter(species %in% c("Bombus auricomus",
                        "Bombus bimaculatus",
                        "Bombus fraternus",
                        "Bombus griseocollis",
                        "Bombus impatiens",
                        "Bombus pensylvanicus",
                        "Bombus vagans",
                        "Bombus variabilis",
                        "Bombus ternarius",
                        "Bombus affinis",
                        "Bombus terricola",
                        "Bombus borealis",
                        "Bombus ashtoni",
                        "Bombus fervidus",
                        "Bombus citrinus",
                        "Bombus rufocinctus")) %>%
  mutate(t_period = ifelse(year <= 1999,
                           "historical",
                           "contemp")) %>%
  mutate(time_period = ifelse(year <= 1930, 
                              "1900-1930",
                              ifelse(year <= 1960,
                                     "1931-1960",
                                     ifelse(year <= 1999,
                                            "1961-1999",
                                            "2000-present"))))

Calculate diversity by county

analysis.bumbles.df %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(county, state, species, t_period) %>%
  summarise(n.bumbles = n()) %>%
  filter(!is.na(t_period)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(county)) %>%
  mutate(state_name = abbr2state(state)) %>%
  filter(species %in% c("Bombus auricomus",
                        "Bombus bimaculatus",
                        "Bombus fraternus",
                        "Bombus griseocollis",
                        "Bombus impatiens",
                        "Bombus pensylvanicus",
                        "Bombus vagans",
                        "Bombus variabilis",
                        "Bombus ternarius",
                        "Bombus affinis",
                        "Bombus terricola",
                        "Bombus borealis",
                        "Bombus ashtoni",
                        "Bombus fervidus",
                        "Bombus citrinus",
                        "Bombus rufocinctus")) %>%
  spread(species,
         n.bumbles,
         fill = 0) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(shannon = diversity(.[, 5:ncol(.)],
                             index = "shannon"),
         simpson = diversity(.[, 5:ncol(.)],
                             index = "simpson")) %>%
  # (county, t_period) %>%
  # summarise(mean_shannon = mean(shannon)) %>%
  dplyr::select(state_name, county, t_period, shannon) %>%
  spread(t_period, shannon) %>%
  filter(!is.na(contemp)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(historical)) %>%
  filter(historical != 0,
         contemp != 0) %>%
  mutate(diff = contemp - historical) %>%
  mutate(direction = ifelse(diff < 0,
                            "lost.diversity",
                            "gained.diversity")) %>%
  group_by(state_name) %>%
  arrange(desc(diff)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(state.county = paste(state_name, 
                              county, 
                              sep = "_")) %>%
  mutate(row_order = factor(.$`state.county`,
                            levels = .$`state.county`)) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_segment(mapping = aes(x = row_order,
                             y = 0,
                             yend = diff,
                             xend = row_order),
               color = "black",
               alpha = 0.75) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = row_order,
                           y = diff,
                           col = direction),
             size = 3) + 
  scale_color_manual(name = "Diversity Trend",
                     labels = c("Gained Diversity", 
                                "Lost Diversity"),
                     values = c("lost.diversity" = "tomato2",
                                "gained.diversity" = "#0e668b")) + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  coord_flip() +
  facet_grid(vars(state_name))
